msgid "Wrong usage: \"Replication allows multiple Tarantool *servers* to work with copies of the same database.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/contributing/docs/style.rst:176
msgid "Correct usage: \"Replication allows multiple Tarantool *instances* to work with copies of the same database.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/contributing/docs/style.rst:180
msgid "Don't use i.e. and e.g."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/contributing/docs/style.rst:182
msgid "Don't use the following contractions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/contributing/docs/style.rst:184
msgid "`\"i.e.\" <https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/i.e.>`_---from the Latin \"id est\". Use \"that is\" or \"which means\" instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/contributing/docs/style.rst:186
msgid "`\"e.g.\" <https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/e.g.>`_---from the Latin \"exempli gratia\". Use \"for example\" or \"such as\" instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../doc/contributing/docs/style.rst:189
msgid "Many people, especially non-native English speakers, aren't familiar with the `\"i.e.\" and \"e.g.\" contractions <https://www.merriam-webster.com/words-at-play/ie-vs-eg-abbreviation-meaning-usage-difference>`_ or don't know the difference between them. For this reason, it's best to avoid using them."
msgstr ""

